				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">This article is about ethno-cultural Tibet.  For the administrative region of China, see <a href="Tibet_Autonomous_Region" title="Tibet Autonomous Region">Tibet Autonomous Region</a>.  For other uses, see <a href="Tibet_(disambiguation)" title="Tibet (disambiguation)">Tibet (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="metadata topicon nopopups" id="protected-icon" style="display:none; right:55px;"><a href="Wikipedia_Protection_policy#semi" title="This article is semi-protected indefinitely in response to an ongoing high risk of vandalism."><img alt="Page semi-protected" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/30px-Padlock-silver.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/40px-Padlock-silver.svg.png 2x" /></a></div>
<table class="metadata mbox-small noprint selfref" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9; width: 22em;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Standard_Tibetan_name.svg/40px-Standard_Tibetan_name.svg.png" width="40" height="25" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Standard_Tibetan_name.svg/60px-Standard_Tibetan_name.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Standard_Tibetan_name.svg/80px-Standard_Tibetan_name.svg.png 2x" /></td>
<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="vertical-align:middle; font-size:95%;"><b>This article contains <a href="Standard_Tibetan" title="Standard Tibetan">Tibetan script</a>.</b> Without proper <a href="Help_Multilingual_support_(Indic)" title="Help:Multilingual support (Indic)">rendering support</a>, you may see <a href="Mojibake" title="Mojibake">question marks, boxes, or other symbols</a> instead of Tibetan characters.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table class="metadata mbox-small noprint selfref" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9; width: 22em;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Zhongwen.svg/40px-Zhongwen.svg.png" width="40" height="20" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Zhongwen.svg/60px-Zhongwen.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Zhongwen.svg/80px-Zhongwen.svg.png 2x" /></td>
<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="vertical-align:middle; font-size:95%;"><b>This article contains <a href="Chinese_language" title="Chinese language">Chinese</a> text.</b> Without proper <a href="Help_Multilingual_support_(East_Asian)" title="Help:Multilingual support (East Asian)">rendering support</a>, you may see <a href="Mojibake" title="Mojibake">question marks, boxes, or other symbols</a> instead of <a href="Chinese_character" title="Chinese character" class="mw-redirect">Chinese characters</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Tibet</b> (<span class="nowrap"><a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d2/En-us-Tibet.ogg" title="Listen"><img alt="Listen" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Speakerlink-new.svg/11px-Speakerlink-new.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Speakerlink-new.svg/17px-Speakerlink-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Speakerlink-new.svg/22px-Speakerlink-new.svg.png 2x" /></a><sup class="noexcerpt"><span style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; padding: 0 .1em;" class="IPA"><a href="../File_En-us-Tibet.ogg" title="File:En-us-Tibet.ogg">i</a></span></sup><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'t' in 'tie'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">t</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/ɨ/ 'e' in 'roses'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">ɨ</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/ˈ/ primary stress follows" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">ˈ</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'b' in 'buy'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">b</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/ɛ/ short 'e' in 'bed'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">ɛ</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'t' in 'tie'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">t</span></a></span><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span></span>; <a href="Tibetan_alphabet" title="Tibetan alphabet">Tibetan</a>: <span lang="bo" style="font-family:'DDC Uchen', Kailash, Jomolhari,'Tibetan Machine Uni'; font-weight:normal; font-size:130%;" xml:lang="bo">བོད་</span>,&#160;<a href="Wylie_transliteration" title="Wylie transliteration">Wylie</a>: <i>Bod</i>, <small>pronounced&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="Help_IPA_for_Tibetan" title="Help:IPA for Tibetan">[pʰø̀ʔ]</a></span>; <a href="Simplified_Chinese_characters" title="Simplified Chinese characters">simplified Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hans" xml:lang="zh-Hans">藏区</span>; <a href="Traditional_Chinese_characters" title="Traditional Chinese characters">traditional Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hant" xml:lang="zh-Hant">藏區</span>; <a href="Pinyin" title="Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <em>Zàngqū</em>) is a <a href="Tibetan_Plateau" title="Tibetan Plateau">plateau region</a> in Asia, north-east of the <a href="Himalaya" title="Himalaya" class="mw-redirect">Himalayas</a>. It is the traditional homeland of the <a href="Tibetan_people" title="Tibetan people">Tibetan people</a> as well as some other ethnic groups such as <a href="Monpa_people" title="Monpa people">Monpas</a>, <a href="Qiang_people" title="Qiang people">Qiang</a>, and <a href="Lhoba" title="Lhoba" class="mw-redirect">Lhobas</a>, and is now also inhabited by considerable numbers of <a href="Han_Chinese" title="Han Chinese">Han</a> and <a href="Hui_people" title="Hui people">Hui people</a>. Tibet is the highest region on earth, with an average elevation of 4,900 metres (16,000&#160;ft).</p>
